&lt;li&gt;Prepare and process semi-monthly payroll timely and accurately for U.S. employees through ADP and review monthly international payroll prepared by the local accounting team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure employee 401(k), HSA, and FSA deductions are correct at each pay period.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor timecard submission and approval process for hourly employees.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with HR to obtain and track payroll data including salary adjustments, special payments, new hire additions, terminations, and healthcare payroll contributions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconcile payroll related GLs including pto, bonus, prepaid, accrued expenses, payroll liabilities, and employee benefits during the month-end process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Import and reconcile payroll journal entries in Netsuite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process and submit quarterly employee stock option grants on Carta.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process stock exercises and calculate related tax withholding for payroll reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with accounts payable to review and approve vendor bills in NetSuite and employee expense reports in Expensify.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain solid understanding of all federal and state payroll tax laws related to wages, garnishments, benefits, leave of absence, 401(k), HSA, FSA, relocation benefits, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle and resolve tax notices/inquiries as needed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with tax and unemployment registrations for new states.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify quarter and year-end payroll tax filings with ADP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with annual audit requests from external auditors related to areas of responsibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform ad-hoc projects, as needed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
